      comments: 'https://theintercept.com/2019/06/07/pfas-chemicals-maine-sludge/#comments',
      content: '<p>The evidence of PFAS in sludge comes just days after an FDA investigation revealed that the nonstick compounds had made their way into some foods.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theintercept.com/2019/06/07/pfas-chemicals-maine-sludge/">Toxic PFAS Chemicals Found in Maine Farms Fertilized With Sewage Sludge</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theintercept.com">The Intercept</a>.</p>\n',
