      pubDate: 'Tue, 11 Jun 2019 15:47:26 +0000',
      'content:encoded': '<p>WASHINGTON &#x2014; Doctors should offer a daily HIV prevention pill to healthy people who are at high risk of getting infected with the virus, an influential health care panel <a href="https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jama/fullarticle/2735509">recommended</a> Tuesday.</p>\n<p>The new guidelines aim to help cut the nearly 40,000 new HIV infections in the U.S. each year.</p><p><a href="https://www.statnews.com/2019/06/11/daily-hiv-prevention-pill-urged-for-healthy-people-at-risk/?utm_campaign=rss">Read the rest&hellip;</a></p>',
