      'content:encoded': '<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The NASH ambitions of Cymabay Therapeutics (<a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=cbay+ticker&amp;oq=CBAY+ticker&amp;aqs=chrome.0.0l2.3816j0j4&amp;sourceid=chrome&amp;ie=UTF-8">CBAY</a>) hit a wall Tuesday with the negative outcome of a mid-stage clinical trial.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In the Phase 2 study, three oral doses of its lead drug, called seladelpar, all performed worse than a placebo, based on a non-invasive imaging test that measures decreases in liver fat. The study had enrolled 181 patients with moderate stage of NASH and treated them for 12 weeks. </span></p><p><a href="https://www.statnews.com/2019/06/11/cymabays-nash-drug-ambitions-dealt-serious-setback-with-negative-study-results/?utm_campaign=rss">Continue to STAT Plus to read the full story&hellip;</a></p>',
